  "prompt": "What is a good substitute for chipotle powder?",
  "response": "Here are several good substitutes for chipotle powder:\n\n1. Smoked paprika\n- Most similar in flavor profile\n- Adds smokiness without as much heat\n- Best 1:1 replacement\n\n2. Ancho chili powder\n- Mild heat and slightly sweet flavor\n- Good alternative if you want less spice\n\n3. Regular chili powder\n- Adds heat but lacks smokiness\n- Can mix with a bit of liquid smoke for similar effect\n\n4. Cayenne pepper\n- Provides heat\n- Lacks smokiness, so consider adding smoked paprika\n\n5. Hot sauce (like Tabasco Chipotle)\n- Provides similar flavor and heat\n- Adjust liquid content in recipe\n\n6. Fresh or canned chipotle peppers in adobo sauce\n- Most authentic flavor\n- Can be blended or ground into a powder\n- More intense flavor than powder\n\n7. Gochugaru (Korean red pepper flakes)\n- Smoky and slightly sweet\n- Different flavor profile but can work in some dishes\n\nThe best substitute depends on your specific recipe and desired flavor profile.",
